{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product of a constant (2023) and an arbitrary integer n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of a multiple of 2023. Since 2023 is odd, this is related to the properties of the cyclic group or the structure of powers of 2 modulo 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "modular_structure_helper",
      "instructions": "Analyze the multiplicative order of 2 modulo 2023. Determine the structure of the group (Z/2023Z)* and identify if there are specific properties of the powers of 2 that can be used to construct a number with a low Hamming weight. Specifically, investigate if there exists an n such that 2023 * n = 2^a - 1 or 2^a + 2^b, etc."
    },
    {
      "label": "weight_minimization_helper",
      "instructions": "Investigate the minimum Hamming weight $w(m)$ for multiples $m$ of a given odd integer $d$. For $d=2023$, test the possibility of $w(2023 \cdot n) = 1$ (impossible as 2023 is not a power of 2), $w(2023 \cdot n) = 2$ (requires $2^a \equiv \pm 2^b \pmod{2023}$), and $w(2023 \cdot n) = 3$ (requires $2^a \pm 2^b \pm 2^c \equiv 0 \pmod{2023}$). Use the properties of the order of 2 modulo the prime factors of 2023 (7, 17, 17) to determine the smallest possible weight."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent should combine the results by first determining the order of 2 modulo 2023 (or its components) to rule out weights 1 and 2. Then, using the modular constraints found, check if a weight of 3 is achievable by solving the congruence $2^a + 2^b + 2^c \equiv 0 \pmod{2023}$ or similar combinations. The smallest weight that satisfies the modular arithmetic requirements will be the final answer."
}
```

